hands_on_practices.solution:
We work in ambient Minkowski space with $\eta_{AB}=\text{diag}(-1,1,1,1)$. The hypersurface is $\Phi(X)=\eta_{AB}X^AX^B-\alpha^2=0$.

1. Unit normal:
$$
n_A=\frac{1}{\alpha}\frac{\partial\Phi}{\partial X^A}
=\frac{2\eta_{AB}X^B}{2\alpha}
=\frac{X_A}{\alpha}
$$
So $n^A=\eta^{BA}n_B=X^A/\alpha$ and $n_An^A=\frac{X_AX^A}{\alpha^2}=\frac{\alpha^2}{\alpha^2}=1$.

2. Extrinsic curvature:
$$
K_{ab}=e_a^Ae_b^B\nabla_A n_B
=e_a^Ae_b^B\partial_A\left(\frac{X_B}{\alpha}\right)
=\frac{1}{\alpha}e_a^Ae_b^B\eta_{BA}
=\frac{g_{ab}}{\alpha}
$$
where $g_{ab}=\eta_{AB}e_a^Ae_b^B$.

3. Raising indices:
$$
K^{ab}=g^{ac}g^{bd}K_{cd}
=\frac{g^{ab}}{\alpha}
$$

4. Contraction:
$$
K_{ab}K^{ab}
=\frac{1}{\alpha^2}g_{ab}g^{ab}
=\frac{3}{\alpha^2}
$$
since $g_{ab}$ is 3-dimensional.
